  - name: PATIENTSURVEY_DICT.Q53_HAS_PCP
    conditions:
      - questionText:
          EN: |
            <p>We will now ask questions about the patient’s access to a primary care provider.</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is about the Patient’s Primary Care Utilization. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies. A primary care provider is your first contact healthcare provider (i.e., general practitioner doctor) for an undiagnosed concern or continuing care of varied medical conditions.</p><p>53. Do you have a primary care provider?</p>
          FIL: |
            <p>Magtatanong kami ngayon tungkol sa access ng pasyente sa isang primary care provider.</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is about the Patient’s Primary Care Utilization. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies. A primary care provider is your first contact healthcare provider (i.e., general practitioner doctor) for an undiagnosed concern or continuing care of varied medical conditions.</p><p>Mayroon ba kayong tagapagbigay ng pangunahing pangangalagang pangkalusugan (primary care provider)?</p>
          BCL: |
            <p>We will now ask questions about the patient’s access to a primary care provider.</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is about the Patient’s Primary Care Utilization. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies. A primary care provider is your first contact healthcare provider (i.e., general practitioner doctor) for an undiagnosed concern or continuing care of varied medical conditions.</p><p>Igwa ba kamo ki primary care provider?</p>
          BIS: |
            <p>We will now ask questions about the patient’s access to a primary care provider.</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is about the Patient’s Primary Care Utilization. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies. A primary care provider is your first contact healthcare provider (i.e., general practitioner doctor) for an undiagnosed concern or continuing care of varied medical conditions.</p><p>Aduna ba kay primary care provider?</p>
          CEB: |
            <p>We will now ask questions about the patient’s access to a primary care provider.</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is about the Patient’s Primary Care Utilization. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies. A primary care provider is your first contact healthcare provider (i.e., general practitioner doctor) for an undiagnosed concern or continuing care of varied medical conditions.</p><p>A primary care provider is your first contact healthcare provider (i.e., general practitioner doctor) for an undiagnosed concern or continuing care of varied medical conditions</p>
          WAR: |
            <p>We will now ask questions about the patient’s access to a primary care provider.</p><p class="instruction">Note to enumerator [do not read]: This section is about the Patient’s Primary Care Utilization. Ask all questions in this section unless a skip rule applies. A primary care provider is your first contact healthcare provider (i.e., general practitioner doctor) for an undiagnosed concern or continuing care of varied medical conditions.</p><p>Mayda ka ba panguna nga nag-aataman?</p>
